cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE

The paper proposes an evolutionary algorithm for solving many-objective optimization problems, which involves optimization, machine learning, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses performance metrics to evaluate the proposed algorithm, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for assigning rank values to solutions, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves designing a linear assignment mechanism, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for estimating the Utopian Pareto front, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
